Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.63,0:00:28.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Propelled forward by the \Nyears spent together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:30.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Charging full speed ahead \Nwithout slowing the pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.46,0:00:33.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious visible mirage \Ntriggers an invisible case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.71,0:00:37.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.47,0:00:39.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.99,0:02:24.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)}Mirage of the Disappearing Angel
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.57,0:02:22.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mirage of the Disappearing Angel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.99,0:02:27.20,Agency,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.94,0:02:27.20,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.40,0:02:31.86,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to find your missing husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.86,0:02:36.21,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. This is my husband Aoki Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.51,0:02:42.97,Artist,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Aoki Satoru (52)\NArtist
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.70,0:02:38.32,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Aoki is an artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.32,0:02:43.18,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He's left to paint before without \Ntelling me where he was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.47,0:02:49.14,Wife,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Aoki Midori (54)\NAoki's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.63,0:02:48.92,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But he always reported his progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.55,0:02:52.56,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,He'd sent photos of his canvas every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.82,0:02:54.01,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.01,0:02:56.07,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,And that stopped the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.29,0:02:59.57,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. This is the last image I received.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.99,0:03:01.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:03.07,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a strange painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.21,0:03:05.33,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,How do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.70,0:03:09.83,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Aoki only paints what he \Nsees with his own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.38,0:03:14.59,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,But that painting is otherworldly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.85,0:03:16.11,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:18.14,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Did he change his style?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.27,0:03:22.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know where Aoki-san is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.18,0:03:26.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The water's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.49,0:03:29.27,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure this is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.62,0:03:30.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.42,0:03:33.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Those light blue waves he painted
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.59,0:03:36.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,are a natural phenomenon called \Na "firefly squid suicide."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.17,0:03:44.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Schools of glowing firefly squids only \Nwash up on the beach in Toyama Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.72,0:03:48.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was last observed here on this beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.97,0:03:51.76,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty obscure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.76,0:03:53.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-I saw it on TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.06,0:03:55.14,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:57.78,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But how will we find him now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.78,0:04:01.37,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start by investigating nearby lodgings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:12.81,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.18,0:04:15.81,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.99,0:04:21.28,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is painter \NAoki Satoru, fifty-two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.53,0:04:27.82,Police,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Detective Sawada (29)\NToyama Police
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.53,0:04:27.82,Police2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Inspector Sakai (58)\NToyama Police
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.55,0:04:22.45,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.45,0:04:25.82,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You identified him rather quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:27.58,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Yes, because
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.94,0:04:32.75,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,his wife was here looking \Nfor him with a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.75,0:04:35.37,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Detective Mori Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.79,0:04:37.02,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:39.67,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! The Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.67,0:04:41.30,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Did he drown?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.58,0:04:48.34,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Probably. He died last \Nnight between 8 and 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.34,0:04:51.85,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,The seas were rough last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:55.31,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And we found this in his jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.49,0:04:57.56,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,So he was drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.85,0:05:01.58,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,According to his wife, \NAoki-san had a bad leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.58,0:05:04.34,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,He dragged one leg as he walked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.79,0:05:08.07,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,He probably tripped and fell into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.07,0:05:09.09,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Actuallyâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.09,0:05:10.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.73,0:05:14.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This man has a bruise on his cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:15.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.26,0:05:17.68,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,He might have gotten it \Nwhen he fell into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.68,0:05:21.56,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible someone hit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.56,0:05:22.35,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.35,0:05:25.01,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Wandering around the crime scene again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.51,0:05:31.72,Fisherman,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Ishiguro Chuji (57)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:33.02,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:36.31,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,A local fisherman named Ishiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.68,0:05:40.06,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,He's a hard worker, but he fights a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:43.36,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:46.19,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,We're the police who contacted you earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.43,0:05:53.53,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes. Aoki-san has been staying \Nhere since two weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.20,0:05:56.00,Manager,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Hayashi Taro (57)\NHotel Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.53,0:05:56.20,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I had no idea he'd died...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.09,0:06:00.28,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know if you need anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.28,0:06:01.35,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.27,0:06:03.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:05.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.50,0:06:12.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I found Aoki-san's painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:16.08,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What's it doing in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:20.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sunlight, dust, and changing temperatures \Nare bad for oil paintings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.46,0:06:23.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why he kept it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.48,0:06:27.24,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,That's the painting he sent me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.47,0:06:29.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:30.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He added something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:31.95,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.47,0:06:33.64,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.64,0:06:35.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's something in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.30,0:06:39.58,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be our house?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.34,0:06:43.25,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,It does look similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.48,0:06:47.39,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't this look like an \Nangel ascending into the sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.39,0:06:52.76,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The white thing under it must \Nbe a soul led by the angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.10,0:06:57.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought Aoki-san only \Npainted what he saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.74,0:07:00.02,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably drunk and hallucinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.41,0:07:06.61,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he predicted he'd \Nbe called to heaven soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:14.49,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's Aoki's digital camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.93,0:07:19.27,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,He photographed everything he painted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:22.18,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,He painted from those photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:24.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:25.71,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.77,0:07:28.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.21,0:07:29.90,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:34.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The photo he painted from has been erased!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.09,0:07:35.57,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.57,0:07:39.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The firefly squid suicide \Nhappened ten days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.55,0:07:42.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no data from that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.25,0:07:43.50,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.50,0:07:47.02,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no folder for May 6th.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.42,0:07:50.86,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,What? The digital camera's \Ndata had been erased?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.16,0:07:54.08,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Do you remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.75,0:08:02.25,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, \Nlast night around midnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.27,0:08:05.61,DCItalic,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.65,0:08:11.06,DCItalic,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Aoki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.45,0:08:17.48,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was already dead by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.48,0:08:23.72,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't see Aoki-san, \Nbut possibly the man who killed him instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.72,0:08:26.59,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:27.81,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.81,0:08:29.68,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,It was dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.68,0:08:34.24,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,He was dragging one foot, \Nso I thought it was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.60,0:08:35.86,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.86,0:08:40.03,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer disguised himself as the \Nvictim and came to erase the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.03,0:08:43.54,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Something incriminating \Nmust've been in the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.54,0:08:44.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.62,0:08:44.90,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.90,0:08:47.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They must be psychic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.76,0:08:48.90,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.90,0:08:50.34,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.34,0:08:54.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They went right to Aoki-san's room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.56,0:08:58.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Only a psychic would've \Nknown where his room was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.36,0:09:00.22,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.59,0:09:04.68,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,With all the other rooms here, it's \Nimpossible to head straight to that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.01,0:09:10.69,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,So the murderer had visited \NAoki-san's room before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:18.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,His wife seemed pretty depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.77,0:09:21.64,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Should we have let her go home by herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.49,0:09:25.80,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Her husband's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.80,0:09:27.22,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,She can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.22,0:09:30.78,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to find who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.45,0:09:35.22,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:39.47,Parttimer,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Akagi Yosuke (21)\NPermanent Part-Timer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.70,0:09:39.47,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I just told the police about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.72,0:09:42.89,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I'm not with them...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.28,0:09:48.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,His wife asked you to trace her \Nhusband's last steps, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.97,0:09:50.56,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:55.86,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, yeah, I met Aoki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.86,0:09:59.60,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking for my missing girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.60,0:10:02.08,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I visited that hotel the day before last
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:05.08,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,to hand out these fliers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.39,0:10:07.51,DCItalic,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.51,0:10:10.47,DCItalic,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's hard, but don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.47,0:10:12.75,DCItalic,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.61,0:10:17.44,DCItalic,AOKI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.72,0:10:25.28,DCItalic,AOKI,0000,0000,0000,,She's long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.28,0:10:27.03,DCItalic,AOKI,0000,0000,0000,,Give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.03,0:10:28.64,DCItalic,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.61,0:10:31.83,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It made me furious!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.58,0:10:35.15,DCMain,YOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,But I haven't seen him since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:38.15,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.36,0:10:44.16,Traveler,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,0)}Shirakawa Kazushi (49)\NTraveler
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.42,0:10:44.16,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I saw him two nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.48,0:10:50.17,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,I was walking along the beach \Nto witness the famous mirage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.43,0:10:51.85,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,That's when...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.64,0:11:01.18,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,He looked deep in thought, \Nlike he was contemplating suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.69,0:11:03.93,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,So I spoke to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.41,0:11:06.87,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,We got along quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:10.19,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,That night we got drunk in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.43,0:11:12.45,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.30,0:11:15.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:18.07,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.55,0:11:22.53,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,You can't look through people's stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.53,0:11:23.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.80,0:11:28.18,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Did Aoki-san kill himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.69,0:11:31.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:36.23,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like these, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.23,0:11:38.17,DCMain,CLERK,0000,0000,0000,,Are they gifts for your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.49,0:11:41.17,DCMain,KAZUSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, for my wife and daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:48.31,DCMain,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.40,0:11:51.73,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,You're the last one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.39,0:12:00.82,DCMain,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,I saw him yesterday morning when I was \Ndelivering fresh fish to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.62,0:12:05.50,DCItalic,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't touched it at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.50,0:12:08.84,DCItalic,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. He just didn't want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.84,0:12:09.92,DCItalic,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.92,0:12:11.08,DCItalic,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.48,0:12:15.71,DCMain,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Us fisherman risk our lives to catch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.71,0:12:20.20,DCMain,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't sit quietly while someone wastes it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.20,0:12:23.21,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,So you went to his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.21,0:12:26.47,DCMain,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I didn't lay a finger on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.47,0:12:29.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd you get those scars?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.82,0:12:34.35,DCMain,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,This? I was in an accident \Nat sea three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.70,0:12:37.86,DCMain,CHUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, I haven't had full control.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.87,0:12:47.62,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.16,0:12:51.37,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,None of them have alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.74,0:12:55.25,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really a murder, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.25,0:12:57.79,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Or an accident? Or a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.20,0:12:59.21,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:01.22,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.22,0:13:04.97,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What are they looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.24,0:13:08.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably the spring mirage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:11.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uozu is famous for its mirages, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.42,0:13:14.01,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mirage?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.01,0:13:15.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could that have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.94,0:13:18.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.36,0:13:26.99,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm exhausted!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.38,0:13:30.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We were walking around all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.21,0:13:37.00,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find whoever erased the \Nvideo from Aoki-san's camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.99,0:13:39.65,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:41.38,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.92,0:13:43.76,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,It's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.43,0:13:46.26,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,This looks delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.55,0:13:50.10,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I caught these fish this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:13:53.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? You fish, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.28,0:13:54.66,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.66,0:13:57.02,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be a fisherman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.35,0:13:59.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then I have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.57,0:14:04.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Does Ishiguro-san always \Nwear a black hat at sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.34,0:14:06.78,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He calls it his lucky charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.78,0:14:07.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:09.66,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.88,0:14:15.50,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Before you leave, why not watch them \Nfish for firefly squids at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:19.27,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,The ocean glows blue. \NIt's incredibly romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.24,0:14:21.79,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain the butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.06,0:14:24.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.18,0:14:25.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:25.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.64,0:14:28.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.65,0:14:34.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.32,0:14:36.10,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.47,0:14:37.86,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.86,0:14:41.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan asked me to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.83,0:14:44.09,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.57,0:14:46.53,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. I'll keep an eye out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:47.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.26,0:14:54.04,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,It's 2 in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.04,0:14:55.87,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really going?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.10,0:14:58.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,They leave at 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.36,0:15:00.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.53,0:15:02.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:04.90,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing. Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.48,0:15:32.20,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,This ends now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.36,0:15:36.16,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.36,0:15:39.79,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, is he really the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.79,0:15:40.41,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.58,0:15:44.31,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You told us the murderer would be coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.08,0:15:50.38,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot pot, beer, and sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:53.61,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.61,0:15:56.89,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I set a trap for the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.37,0:16:02.98,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Once I return to Tokyo, \NI could restore the erased data.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:06.73,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I kept everyone \Naway from this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.09,0:16:10.07,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,And the murderer showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.49,0:16:15.74,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, \Nhotel manager Hayashi Taro-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.96,0:16:18.29,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.29,0:16:21.75,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm protecting the camera like you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:26.41,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer must meet two conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.72,0:16:29.33,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,First, he must be left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.33,0:16:31.88,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Second, he must be able to operate a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.17,0:16:33.05,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.55,0:16:38.26,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Someone had struck the \Nvictim on his right cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.77,0:16:43.27,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he caught a \Nleft-handed punch to the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.47,0:16:46.57,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But what about operating a boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.57,0:16:50.78,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer erased the data \Nfrom Aoki-san's camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.11,0:16:58.23,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there was evidence \Nleading to the murderer in the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.23,0:16:59.45,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, the painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.63,0:17:00.99,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.02,0:17:06.59,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,We believed the painting \Ndepicted a hallucination
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.59,0:17:09.65,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,of an angel leading a soul into heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:13.80,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,But Aoki-san only paints what he sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.15,0:17:17.18,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, it must be real.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:21.19,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What? But it looks totally fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:22.74,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mirage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:24.44,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,A mirage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.44,0:17:29.81,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,In spring, the air near the water's \Nsurface cools and becomes dense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.23,0:17:31.76,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Light is refracted,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.76,0:17:38.32,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,causing a mirage reflecting the actual \Nscenery upside-down to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.75,0:17:41.77,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if you turn \Nthe painting upside-down,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.77,0:17:45.44,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,you'll see what actually happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.36,0:17:48.46,DCMain,SAWADA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.86,0:17:52.63,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The white house painted \Nthere is a fishing boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.07,0:17:57.02,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The angel flying into the sky is a \Nwoman being pushed into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.38,0:18:02.64,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,And the soul below it is \Nthe murderer's white hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.98,0:18:08.14,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this painting \Ndepicts a terrible murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:20.28,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,While reviewing his painting, \NAoki-san must have realized the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.89,0:18:27.54,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,He told Akagi-kun to give up on his \Ngirlfriend, gazed thoughtfully at the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:33.85,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,and had no appetite for \Nbreakfast because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.85,0:18:36.30,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is the woman who was murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.73,0:18:41.41,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The firefly squid suicide in the \Npainting happened ten days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.41,0:18:45.22,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Akagi-kun's girlfriend \Ndisappeared on the same day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.86,0:18:50.41,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Based on her haircut and \Nclothes, it's probably her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.99,0:18:55.55,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Aoki-san was killed because he realized this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.88,0:19:01.24,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer must be a left-handed \Nman who could operate a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.88,0:19:04.61,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Akagi-kun was handing out \Nfliers with his left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.61,0:19:07.50,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,He's left-handed, but can't operate a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.12,0:19:12.00,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Shirakawa-san locked his \Nsuitcase with his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.62,0:19:16.96,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Ishiguro-san, who could operate a boat, \Ndoesn't have full control of his left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.31,0:19:21.47,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,And when he goes to sea, \Nhe wears a black hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.94,0:19:25.97,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the only \Nman who knew Aoki-san
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.27,0:19:28.91,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,was staying in this room and \Nmeets these conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.69,0:19:32.91,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,is the man who held his chopsticks
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.91,0:19:36.48,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,in his left hand and showed \Nus the fish he caught himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.79,0:19:40.36,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,The hotel manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.58,0:19:43.49,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that's not enough to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:46.12,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier you mentioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.54,0:19:53.12,DCItalic,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find whoever erased the \Nvideo from Aoki-san's camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.53,0:19:56.75,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,That camera can record videos.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.39,0:20:02.51,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know it was a video \Nand not a photo that had been erased?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.97,0:20:10.30,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Only the late Aoki-san and the man \Nwho erased the data would know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:15.40,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What about the suspicious figure he saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.79,0:20:20.40,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,An imaginary person to direct \Nsuspicion away from himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.93,0:20:26.53,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,At first, it was an accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.54,0:20:52.85,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think anyone was filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.12,0:20:58.28,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,He told me to turn myself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.92,0:21:01.03,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,To atone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.24,0:21:02.47,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.03,0:21:15.25,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I erased all the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.71,0:21:17.25,DCMain,TARO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.25,0:21:20.46,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.79,0:22:46.84,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.29,0:22:48.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.74,0:22:52.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Aoki-san helped us solve a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.21,0:22:56.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I think he saved a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.39,0:22:56.85,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:22:59.60,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.80,0:23:01.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I mean Shirakawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.59,0:23:08.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He came to see the mirage, but he \Ndidn't have binoculars or a camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.79,0:23:13.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He only had two bottles of \Nsleeping pills in his bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.88,0:23:18.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He probably went to Uozu to kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.90,0:23:22.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But he was buying gifts for \Nhis family at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.67,0:23:25.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof he changed his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.38,0:23:31.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Aoki-san probably prevented his suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.80,0:23:34.97,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.69,0:23:42.02,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.48,0:23:43.87,DCMain,MIDORI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.59,0:23:51.11,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Kusuda Rikumichi? Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.24,0:23:55.45,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,The organization spy who infiltrated \NMizunashi Rena's hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.45,0:23:57.98,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.98,0:24:03.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the FBI to keep it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.61,0:24:05.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The organization's man Bourbon...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.92,0:24:08.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro Toru is conducting an investigation.
